of 1990, referred to in subsec. (c)(2)(B), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/624/s2324"},"text":"section 2324 of Pub. L. 101–624","children":[],"tail":", which was set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1926"},"text":"section 1926 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127/tVII/s703"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127, title VII, § 703","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-04"},"text":"Apr. 4, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1108"},"text":"110 Stat. 1108","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"ideff414a6-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/354/s232"},"text":"section 232 of Pub. L. 103–354","children":[],"tail":". Prior to amendment of this section by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334","children":[],"tail":", subsec. (b)(2), formerly (b)(3), of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/354/s232"},"text":"section 232 of Pub. L. 103–354","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees. See 2018 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ideff414a7-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (2) amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees, and text of par. (1) read as follows: “The Rural Utilities Service shall be headed by an Administrator who shall be appointed by the President.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166/s2/a/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166, § 2(a)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166/s2/a/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166, § 2(a)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (C), which directed that subsec. (b)(1) of this section be amended by striking out par. (2) and redesignating par. (3) as (2), was executed by making the amendment to subsec. (b) of this section, to reflect the probable intent of Congress. See Codification note above. Prior to amendment, text of par. (2) read as follows: “Any official who is serving as Administrator of the Rural Electrification Administration on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"October 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", and who was appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) may be considered to be serving in the successor position established under paragraph (1); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) shall not be required to be reappointed to that position by reason of the enactment of this Act.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/127"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–127","children":[],"tail":" substituted “section 1932(b)” for “section 1932(b)(2)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ideff414a8-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ideff414a9-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2012 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–166","children":[],"tail":" effective 60 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2012","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to appointments made on and after that effective date, including any nomination pending in the Senate on that date, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/166/s6/a"},"text":"section 6(a) of Pub. L. 112–166","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s113"},"text":"section 113 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
